#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an6.43"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.43:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.43:0.2"
msgid "5. Dhammikavagga "
msgstr "5. About Dhammika "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.43:0.3"
msgid "43. Nāgasutta "
msgstr "43. The Giant "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.345, sc1
msgctxt "an6.43:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.43:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms. "

msgctxt "an6.43:1.3"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then, after the meal, on his return from alms-round, he addressed Venerable Ānanda, "

msgctxt "an6.43:1.4"
msgid "“āyāmānanda, yena pubbārāmo migāramātupāsādo tenupasaṅkamissāma divāvihārāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to the Eastern Monastery, the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother for the day’s meditation.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.43:1.5"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an6.43:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ yena pubbārāmo migāramātupāsādo tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "So the Buddha went with Ānanda to the Eastern Monastery. "

msgctxt "an6.43:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "In the late afternoon the Buddha came out of retreat and addressed Ānanda, "

msgctxt "an6.43:2.3"
msgid "“āyāmānanda, yena pubbakoṭṭhako tenupasaṅkamissāma gattāni parisiñcitun”ti. "
msgstr "“Come, Ānanda, let’s go to the eastern gate to bathe.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.43:2.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Ānanda replied. "

msgctxt "an6.43:2.5"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ yena pubbakoṭṭhako tenupasaṅkami gattāni parisiñcituṃ. "
msgstr "So the Buddha went with Ānanda to the eastern gate to bathe. "

msgctxt "an6.43:2.6"
msgid "Pubbakoṭṭhake gattāni parisiñcitvā paccuttaritvā ekacīvaro aṭṭhāsi gattāni pubbāpayamāno. "
msgstr "When he had bathed and emerged from the water he stood in one robe drying himself. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.346, sc3
#. VAR: mahātūriyatāḷitavāditena → mahāturiyatālita … (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.43:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena rañño pasenadissa kosalassa seto nāma nāgo mahātūriyatāḷitavāditena pubbakoṭṭhakā paccuttarati. "
msgstr "Now, at that time King Pasenadi had a giant bull elephant called “White”. It emerged from the eastern gate to the beating and playing of musical instruments. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.43:3.2"
msgid "Apissu taṃ jano disvā evamāha: "
msgstr "When people saw it they said, "

# NOTE: BB includes the extra phrase “nago vata bho nago” here, however, it is absent from most editions so I don’t include it.
msgctxt "an6.43:3.3"
msgid "“abhirūpo vata bho rañño nāgo; dassanīyo vata bho rañño nāgo; pāsādiko vata, bho, rañño nāgo, kāyupapanno vata bho rañño nāgo”ti. "
msgstr "“The royal giant is so handsome! The royal giant is so good-looking! The royal giant is so lovely! The royal giant has such a huge body!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.43:3.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā udāyī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When they said this, Venerable Udāyī said to the Buddha, "

#. VAR: mahantaṃ brahantaṃ → mahantaṃ bruhantaṃ (bj) | mahattaṃ brahmattaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:3.5"
msgid "“hatthimeva nu kho, bhante, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ kāyupapannaṃ jano disvā evamāha: "
msgstr "“Sir, is it only when they see elephants with such a huge, formidable body that people say: "

#. VAR: kañci → kiñci (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:3.6"
msgid "‘nāgo vata bho nāgo’ti, udāhu aññampi kañci mahantaṃ brahantaṃ kāyupapannaṃ jano disvā evamāha: ‘nāgo vata bho nāgo’”ti? "
msgstr "‘A giant, such a giant’? Or do they say it when they see any other creatures with huge, formidable bodies?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.43:3.7"
msgid "“Hatthimpi kho, udāyi, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ kāyupapannaṃ jano disvā evamāha: "
msgstr "“Udāyī, when they see elephants with such a huge, formidable body people say: "

msgctxt "an6.43:3.8"
msgid "‘nāgo vata bho nāgo’ti. "
msgstr "‘A giant, such a giant!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.43:3.9"
msgid "Assampi kho, udāyi, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "And also when they see a horse with a huge, formidable body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.43:3.10"
msgid "goṇampi kho, udāyi, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "When they see a bull with a huge, formidable body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: uragampi → nāgampi (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:3.11"
msgid "uragampi kho, udāyi, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "When they see a snake with a huge, formidable body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.43:3.12"
msgid "rukkhampi kho, udāyi, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "When they see a tree with a huge, formidable body … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.43:3.13"
msgid "manussampi kho, udāyi, mahantaṃ brahantaṃ kāyupapannaṃ jano disvā evamāha: "
msgstr "And when they see a human being with such a huge, formidable body people say: "

msgctxt "an6.43:3.14"
msgid "‘nāgo vata, bho, nāgo’ti. "
msgstr "‘A giant, such a giant!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: By using monstrous I am trying to echo the pun in the text. Not very good, perhaps, but neither is the original!
msgctxt "an6.43:3.15"
msgid "Api ca, udāyi, yo sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya āguṃ na karoti kāyena vācāya manasā, tamahaṃ ‘nāgo’ti brūmī”ti. "
msgstr "But Udāyī, one who does nothing monstrous by way of body, speech, and mind is who I call a ‘giant’ in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an6.43:4.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing! "

msgctxt "an6.43:4.2"
msgid "Yāva subhāsitañcidaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā—"
msgstr "How well said this was by the Buddha: "

msgctxt "an6.43:4.3"
msgid "api ca, udāyi, yo sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya āguṃ na karoti kāyena vācāya manasā, tamahaṃ ‘nāgo’ti brūmīti. "
msgstr "‘But Udāyī, one who does nothing monstrous by way of body, speech, and mind is who I call a “giant” in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans.’ "

msgctxt "an6.43:4.4"
msgid "Idañca panāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā subhāsitaṃ imāhi gāthāhi anumodāmi—"
msgstr "And I celebrate the well-spoken words of the Buddha with these verses: "

# NOTE: My translation here follows, with a few adjustments, my earlier translation of Thag 15.2.
#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an6.43:5.1"
msgid "Manussabhūtaṃ sambuddhaṃ, "
msgstr "Awakened as a human being, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:5.2"
msgid "attadantaṃ samāhitaṃ; "
msgstr "self-tamed and immersed in samādhi, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:5.3"
msgid "Iriyamānaṃ brahmapathe, "
msgstr "following the spiritual path, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:5.4"
msgid "cittassūpasame rataṃ. "
msgstr "he loves peace of mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an6.43:6.1"
msgid "Yaṃ manussā namassanti, "
msgstr "Revered by people, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:6.2"
msgid "sabbadhammāna pāraguṃ; "
msgstr "gone beyond all things, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: taṃ → naṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.43:6.3"
msgid "Devāpi taṃ namassanti, "
msgstr "even the gods revere him; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:6.4"
msgid "iti me arahato sutaṃ. "
msgstr "so I’ve heard from the perfected one. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an6.43:7.1"
msgid "Sabbasaṃyojanātītaṃ, "
msgstr "He has transcended all fetters "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: nibbanamāgataṃ → nibbāna … (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.43:7.2"
msgid "vanā nibbanamāgataṃ; "
msgstr "and escaped from entanglements. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: nekkhammarataṃ → nekkhamme rataṃ (si)
msgctxt "an6.43:7.3"
msgid "Kāmehi nekkhammarataṃ, "
msgstr "Delighting to renounce sensual pleasures, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:7.4"
msgid "muttaṃ selāva kañcanaṃ. "
msgstr "he’s freed like gold from stone. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an6.43:8.1"
msgid "Sabbe accarucī nāgo, "
msgstr "That giant outshines all, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:8.2"
msgid "himavāññe siluccaye; "
msgstr "like the Himalaya beside other mountains. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:8.3"
msgid "Sabbesaṃ nāganāmānaṃ, "
msgstr "Of all those named ‘giant’, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:8.4"
msgid "saccanāmo anuttaro. "
msgstr "he is truly named, supreme. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
#. VAR: vo → te (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:9.1"
msgid "Nāgaṃ vo kittayissāmi, "
msgstr "I’ll extol the giant for you, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:9.2"
msgid "na hi āguṃ karoti so; "
msgstr "for he does nothing monstrous. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:9.3"
msgid "Soraccaṃ avihiṃsā ca, "
msgstr "Gentleness and harmlessness "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:9.4"
msgid "pādā nāgassa te duve. "
msgstr "are two feet of the giant. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "an6.43:10.1"
msgid "Tapo ca brahmacariyaṃ, "
msgstr "Austerity and celibacy "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:10.2"
msgid "caraṇā nāgassa tyāpare; "
msgstr "are his two other feet. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:10.3"
msgid "Saddhāhattho mahānāgo, "
msgstr "Faith is the giant’s trunk, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:10.4"
msgid "upekkhāsetadantavā. "
msgstr "and equanimity his white tusks. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "an6.43:11.1"
msgid "Sati gīvā siro paññā, "
msgstr "Mindfulness is his neck, his head is wisdom—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:11.2"
msgid "vīmaṃsā dhammacintanā; "
msgstr "inquiry and thinking about principles. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:11.3"
msgid "Dhammakucchisamātapo, "
msgstr "His belly is the sacred hearth of the Dhamma, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:11.4"
msgid "viveko tassa vāladhi. "
msgstr "and his tail is seclusion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "an6.43:12.1"
msgid "So jhāyī assāsarato, "
msgstr "Practicing absorption, enjoying the breath, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: ajjhattaṃ susamāhito → ajjhattūpasamāhito (s1-3) | ajjhattupasamāhito (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:12.2"
msgid "ajjhattaṃ susamāhito; "
msgstr "he is serene within. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:12.3"
msgid "Gacchaṃ samāhito nāgo, "
msgstr "The giant is serene when walking, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:12.4"
msgid "ṭhito nāgo samāhito. "
msgstr "the giant is serene when standing, "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.347, sc13
msgctxt "an6.43:13.1"
msgid "Seyyaṃ samāhito nāgo, "
msgstr "the giant is serene when lying down, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:13.2"
msgid "nisinnopi samāhito; "
msgstr "and when sitting, the giant is serene. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:13.3"
msgid "Sabbattha saṃvuto nāgo, "
msgstr "The giant is restrained everywhere: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:13.4"
msgid "esā nāgassa sampadā. "
msgstr "this is the accomplishment of the giant. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "an6.43:14.1"
msgid "Bhuñjati anavajjāni, "
msgstr "He eats blameless things, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:14.2"
msgid "sāvajjāni na bhuñjati; "
msgstr "he doesn’t eat blameworthy things. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:14.3"
msgid "Ghāsamacchādanaṃ laddhā, "
msgstr "When he gets food and clothes, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:14.4"
msgid "sannidhiṃ parivajjayaṃ. "
msgstr "he avoids storing them up. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "an6.43:15.1"
msgid "Saṃyojanaṃ aṇuṃ thūlaṃ, "
msgstr "Having severed all bonds, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:15.2"
msgid "sabbaṃ chetvāna bandhanaṃ; "
msgstr "fetters large and small, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:15.3"
msgid "Yena yeneva gacchati, "
msgstr "wherever he goes, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:15.4"
msgid "anapekkhova gacchati. "
msgstr "he goes without concern. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "an6.43:16.1"
msgid "Yathāpi udake jātaṃ, "
msgstr "A white lotus, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:16.2"
msgid "puṇḍarīkaṃ pavaḍḍhati; "
msgstr "fragrant and delightful, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Nupalippati → na upalippati (bj, s1, km, pts1) | na upalimpati (s2, s3) | nupalimpati (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:16.3"
msgid "Nupalippati toyena, "
msgstr "sprouts in water and grows there, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:16.4"
msgid "sucigandhaṃ manoramaṃ. "
msgstr "but the water doesn’t cling to it. "

# NOTE: BB has “well-born”, but I suspect lokesu is merely a locative plural metri causa. The parallel line in Tag 15.2 lacks su, inserting a ca instead.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "an6.43:17.1"
msgid "Tatheva loke sujāto, "
msgstr "Just so the Buddha is born in the world, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:17.2"
msgid "buddho loke viharati; "
msgstr "and lives in the world, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:17.3"
msgid "Nupalippati lokena, "
msgstr "but the world doesn’t stick to him, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:17.4"
msgid "toyena padumaṃ yathā. "
msgstr "as the water does not stick to the lotus. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
#. VAR: Mahāginīva jalito → mahāggini pajjalito (bj, s1-3, km) | mahāgini pajjalito (pts1)
msgctxt "an6.43:18.1"
msgid "Mahāginīva jalito, "
msgstr "A great blazing fire "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:18.2"
msgid "anāhārūpasammati; "
msgstr "dies down when the fuel runs out. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Saṅkhāresūpasantesu → aṅgāresu ca santesu (mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:18.3"
msgid "Saṅkhāresūpasantesu, "
msgstr "When the coals have gone out "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:18.4"
msgid "nibbutoti pavuccati. "
msgstr "it’s said to be ‘extinguished’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "an6.43:19.1"
msgid "Atthassāyaṃ viññāpanī, "
msgstr "This simile is taught by the discerning "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:19.2"
msgid "upamā viññūhi desitā; "
msgstr "to express the meaning clearly. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Viññassanti → viññāyanti (s1-3) | viññissanti (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:19.3"
msgid "Viññassanti mahānāgā, "
msgstr "Great giants will understand "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:19.4"
msgid "nāgaṃ nāgena desitaṃ. "
msgstr "what the giant taught the giant. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "an6.43:20.1"
msgid "Vītarāgo vītadoso, "
msgstr "Free of greed, free of hate, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:20.2"
msgid "Vītamoho anāsavo; "
msgstr "free of delusion, undefiled; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an6.43:20.3"
msgid "Sarīraṃ vijahaṃ nāgo, "
msgstr "the giant, giving up his body, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Parinibbissati → parinibbāti (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an6.43:20.4"
msgid "Parinibbissati anāsavo”ti. "
msgstr "will become extinguished without defilements.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.43:20.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

